pageContext.claim: “Unemployment in the United States is at the lowest level it's been in 51 years.”
pageContext.analysis: The unemployment rate is low, but not quite that low. In May 2019, it dipped to 3.6 percent. That ticked up to 3.7 percent in June 2019. Still, the unemployment rate was 3.4 percent 50 years ago in 1969 and the all time low was 2.6 percent in 1953.
